    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Dash Board Panels, Cluster and Switch Panels</title>
        <para>The dash panel, switch panels and driver storage panels are all constructed of injection molded composite
            material. All panels assemble together to make a clean fully functional assembly, enhancing visibility and
            ease of operation, with the ergonomically designed panels. All panels are removable for access to the
            components and assemblies in the driver control area (
            <hotlnk document="s47003_14.xml" xrefid="f4700350">Figure 50</hotlnk>). To remove the dash panels follow the
            procedures as listed.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Dash Panels</para>
            <figure id="f47003143" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g47003143.webp" filename="../figg47/G47003143.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 143. Passenger Side Entry Panel Section</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">PASSENGER SIDE WINDSHIELD WING PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">PASSENGER ENTRY PANEL COVER TOP MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">HEATER FACE PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">PASSENGER SIDE ENTRY DASH COVER PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Beginning at the passenger entry door and step well, locate the dash panel mounting
                    bolts along the leading edge of the step well panel at the lower section of the windshield glass and
                    seal.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the panel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Locate the panel lower edge mounting screws the secure the panel to the entry panel or
                    step well heater panel (if equipped). Loosen and remove the mounting screws.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">With the mounting screws and bolts removed, lift the step well panel cover upward and
                    out.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Dash Panel / Cluster And Right Switch Panel</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Locate and remove the forward edge mounting bolts along the lower windshield seal.
                    Loosen and remove the mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Slide the driver side window forward section open to access the mounting screw at the
                    left hand corner of the dash panel assembly. Loosen and remove the mounting screw.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Locate the right wing switch panel, locate and remove any optional equipment mountings
                    that may be mounted to the right wing switch panel (
                    <hotlnk document="s47003_14.xml" xrefid="f4700351">Figure 51</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f47003144" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g47003144.webp" filename="../figg47/G47003144.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 144. Right Wing Switch Panel Remove</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">RIGHT WING DASH PANEL</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">RIGHT WING SWITCH PANEL</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">SWITCH PANEL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">To remove right wing switch panel, locate the four mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f47003144">Figure 144, Item 3</hotlnk>) attaching the switch panel assembly. Loosen
                    and remove.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the switch panel assembly and disconnect harness connections if necessary.</para>
                <figure id="f47003145" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g47003145.webp" filename="../figg47/G47003145.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="232px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 145. Cluster Attachment Mounting Screws</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">INSTRUMENT CLUSTER</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">CLUSTER MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Locate the cluster assembly.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Locate the cluster mounting screws, loosen and remove.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lift the instrument cluster out to access the harness connections. Disconnect the
                    instrument cluster harness and remove cluster.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Left Hand Driver Switch Panel</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">The left hand switch panel contains the operating controls for many of the bus interior
                    functions (
                    <hotlnk document="s47003_14.xml" xrefid="f4700351">Figure 51, Item 1</hotlnk>). The switch panel
                    assembly must be removed first.
                </para>
                <figure id="f47003146" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic id="g47003146.webp" filename="../figg47/G47003146.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="484px" scalefitheight="408px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 146. Driver Left Hand Switch Panel</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">LEFT WING SWITCH PANEL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">LEFT WING SWITCH PANEL</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">BOOSTER PUMP</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">MASTER DISCONNECT</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">CROSSING GATE</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">MASTER FLASH</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">FLASHER LIGHTS</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">HEADLIGHTS - PARK LIGHTS</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">PANEL LIGHTS</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">RED OVER RIDE</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">TWO POSITION DOOR SWITCH</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER HEATER</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">MID SHIP HEATER</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">REAR HEATER</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Locate the 7 left hand switch panel mounting screws.</para>
                <figure id="f47003147" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic id="g47003147.webp" filename="../figg47/G47003147.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="484px" scalefitheight="408px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 147. Heater Controls (A - Driver Left Wing Heater Control Panel and B - Driver Right
                        Wing Switch Panel
                    </caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">PANEL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">POWER INDICATOR LIGHT</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">BI-LEVEL CONTROL - DEFROSTER/HEATER</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">RECIRCULATION CONTROL</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">HEATER TEMPERATURE CONTROL</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">FAN SPEED</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">DRIVER HEATER SWITCH</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">REAR HEATER SWITCHES</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">BOOSTER PUMP CONTROL SWITCH</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">MID-SHIP HEATERS (UNDER SEAT)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the panel screws.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Lift the switch panel out and disconnect necessary harnesses for removal of the switch
                    panel.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
